cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper is primarily focused on detecting anomalous behavior in federated learning systems, which is a problem related to machine learning and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper deals with detecting malicious clients. Additionally, the paper also involves the use of low-dimensional surrogates of model weight vectors, which is a technique related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the experiments involve training an image classification model, which is a task related to data science (cs.DS).
